# WideBasketFab тАФ RTL expand (mandatory)

## Rule

**WideBasketFab ALWAYS expands from right to left.** The right edge stays fixed; only the left edge moves.

## In merchant tab bar

Layout (last flex child = right edge pinned):

| Phase | Row layout |
|-------|------------|
| loading / collapsed | `[pill flex-1 ┬╖ search 56px ┬╖ slot 56px]` |
| default (expanded) | `[solo pill 56px ┬╖ search 56px ┬╖ slot flex-1]` |

Implementation:

1. **Basket slot** тАФ `margin-inline-start: auto` + tween `flex`/`width` (150ms ease-out). This pins the right edge; width grows **left**.
2. **FAB** (`.wide-basket-fab--in-tab-bar`) тАФ `position: absolute !important; inset-inline-end: 0; width: 100% !important`.
3. **Do NOT** tween FAB `width` in the tab bar тАФ only `padding-inline`.
4. **Do NOT** use `margin-inline-start: auto` on the FAB button (slot only).

## Why flex-grow alone fails

A flex item without `margin-inline-start: auto` grows to the **right** (main axis). RTL expand requires `margin-inline-start: auto` on the **slot** so extra width extends leftward.

Canonical constants: `src/lib/wideBasketFabExpand.ts`.

## Component

`WideBasketFab` root button must expose:

- `data-expand-direction="rtl"`
- `data-expand-anchor="right"`

## Tests

Run `npm test` тАФ `wideBasketFabExpand` + `merchantFloatingTabBarLayout` contracts must pass before marking done.

## Common mistake

Animating FAB `width` from `56px` тЖТ `100%` without `right: 0` anchoring grows from the **left** тАФ wrong.
